(1) Where any tax or interest due from a taxable supplier remains unpaid, the Commissioner-General may, by notice in writing, require any other person— (a) from whom any money is due, or is accruing or may become due, to the supplier ; (b) who holds, or may subsequently hold, money on account of some person for or on account of, or for payment to, the supplier ; or (c) having authority from any person to pay money to the supplier ; to pay that money, or so much as is sufficient to discharge the tax or interest due from the taxable supplier , in the manner directed by the Commissioner-General as and when it would, but for the notice, be or become payable to the supplier .
