(2) Upon service of a notice under this section, the money concerned, to the extent necessary to discharge the tax or interest due from the supplier , is a debt due to the Republic and shall be recoverable at the suit of the Commissioner-General , or any officer authorised by him, in any court of competent jurisdiction; and all claims by the supplier to such money shall, to the like extent, be thereby extinguished.
